# Close loop — never defer

Under **no circumstances** is it OK to leave an identified gap unowned.

## Forbidden outcomes (without active worker transcript ID)

- "may need follow-up", "deferred", "left for next cycle", "handoff", "parent should"
- "orchestrator not delegated", "blocked", "paused until remediation"
- Merging a PR before bot **implement** commits are on the branch that merges
- Reporting **merged** without verifying fix SHAs are on `origin/main`
- `chief:scan` exit **0** while known post-merge code gaps remain

## Required

- Every identified gap: **implemented + on main** OR **open PR with ship bar in flight** in the **same chief cycle**
- After squash merge: `npm run close-loop:check -- --pr <n>` then `npm run close-loop:check -- --post-merge-gap`
- Chief cycle complete only when: no open PRs **or** each has active orchestrator; no post-merge gaps; `chief:scan` **0**; `agent:auditor` no **fail** on `open_loops`

## Commands

```sh
npm run close-loop:check -- --pr <n>          # after merge
npm run close-loop:check -- --post-merge-gap  # scan recent merges
npm run ship:closeout:strict                  # includes close-loop on main
```

Full policy: `~/.cursor/skills/chief-agent/SKILL.md` (Non-negotiable: close every loop).
